Citation.sTitle: Solubility of 3-Chlorophthalic Anhydride and 4-Chlorophthalic Anhydride in Organic Solvents and Solubility of 3-Chlorophthalic Acid and 4-Chlorophthalic Acid in Water from (283.15 to 333.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of 3-chlorophthalic anhydride and 4-chlorophthalic anhydride in ethyl acetate, acetone, and 1,4-dioxane and the solubility of 3-chlorophthalic acid and 4-chlorophthalic acid in water were measured using Schreinemaker s wet residue method at temperatures ranging from (283.15 to 333.15) K at atmospheric pressure. Results of these measurements were correlated with the modified Apelblat equation.
